"analysis": "Previous step loaded all four telemetry files and returned compact aggregates: counts of distinct (cmdb_id, KPI) pairs for metric, trace, and log files (most series have 31 samples across the 19:30–20:00 window), and error_logs.csv appears empty. From that we know which metrics/traces/logs exist per component and that we have complete per-minute coverage for the incident window. Next we must compute global thresholds (using the full available series) for each component-KPI/time-series so we can later filter the incident window and run anomaly detection. This calculation must use the full series (not yet filtered to the incident window) and must be output-bounded.", 
